indicate steric clashes of the ATP state of the Hsp90NTD to the Hsp70NBD (orange; surface/ribbon representation). d, Superposition of the Hsp70ATP conformation (green; PDB ID: 4B9Q75) to the Hsp70CNBD (dark orange). Arrows indicate the two subdomains of Hsp70ATPSBD, which cause serious steric clashes with the Hsp90 in the loading complex shown in e. e, The superimposed Hsp70ATP shown in e is fixed from d and the Hsp90 (dark blue; surface/ribbon
representation) of the GR-loading complex is present. Magenta circles highlight steric clashes caused by the two subdomains of Hsp70ATPSBD (green) to the Hsp90ANTD-MD.

